===Etymology===
French ''[[vallée]]'' < Latin ''vales''.

===Noun===
'''valley''' (''plural:'' [[valleys]])

#An [[elongated]] [[depression]] between [[hill]]s or [[mountain]]s, often with a [[river]] flowing through it.
#The area which drains into a river.
#Any [[structure]] resembling 1, e.g., the meeting point of two [[pitch]]ed [[roof]]s.

